I now have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me compile the comprehensive UX audit and redesign plan.

---

# Comprehensive UX Audit & Visual Redesign Plan for Modular Apartment Planner

## 1. UX Audit: 7 Biggest Problems

### Problem 1: Toolbar Density & Horizontal Overflow
**Severity: Critical**

The toolbar packs 30+ interactive elements into a single 56px row: 8 file/clipboard buttons, 4 model-target segments, 6+ view-mode segments, 13 tool buttons, 7 fixture buttons, 6 toggle buttons, plus labels and dividers. The container uses `overflow-x: auto` (`Toolbar.module.css` line 9), meaning on viewports under ~1400px, content clips off-screen with a barely visible 3px scrollbar. Users cannot see all available tools at once, and the scrollbar is so thin (3px, `rgba(0,0,0,0.10)`) it is effectively invisible.

**Evidence**: `Toolbar.module.css` lines 9-20 (overflow + scrollbar), `Toolbar.jsx` lines 204-430 (30+ buttons rendered inline). At the `@media (max-width: 900px)` breakpoint (line 322), labels are hidden and buttons shrink to 30x30, but the row still overflows.

### Problem 2: No Empty States or Onboarding
**Severity: High**

When a new project is created, the canvas shows a blank grid with no guidance. The sidebar sections show "0" count badges but no helpful text. Empty sections in the sidebar render nothing when collapsed or show raw text like "Draw first truss above beams" (`Sidebar.jsx` line 418) without visual affordance (no icon, no illustration, just plain 12px text styled as a clickable `.item`).

The status bar at the bottom is the only contextual guidance, using monospace text at 11px (`SvgCanvas.module.css` lines 23-41) -- easy to miss.

### Problem 3: Touch & Mobile Inoperability
**Severity: High**

The entire interaction model depends on `onMouseDown/Move/Up` events (`SvgCanvas.jsx` lines 151-199). There are no touch event handlers. The toolbar has no hamburger/collapse pattern. Sidebar and Properties panels use `display: none` toggling (`App.module.css` line 80) with no gesture-based reveal. The 260px sidebar + 280px properties panel leave only ~460px for canvas on a 1000px tablet -- and there is no breakpoint that collapses them automatically. The only responsive breakpoints address 3D preview stacking (1200px) and toolbar compaction (1100px, 900px) -- neither collapses the side panels.

### Problem 4: Input Fields Are Too Compact for Precision Work
**Severity: Medium-High**

All form inputs are 28px tall with 12px font (`InputField.module.css` lines 24-36). For a CAD tool where users frequently type precise millimeter values, this is uncomfortably small. The label width is fixed at 80px (`InputField.module.css` line 9), which truncates longer labels. Number inputs use `JetBrains Mono` at 12px -- good choice but too small. The suffix indicator (mm, m) is 10px (`InputField.module.css` line 56) and easy to overlook.

### Problem 5: Status Bar is Information-Dense but Low-Hierarchy
**Severity: Medium**

The status bar (`SvgCanvas.jsx` lines 681-699) dumps 6-10 items in a flat row: coordinates, zoom, view mode, model target, active tool, phase, bearing, selection count. All use the same 11px JetBrains Mono in `--color-text-secondary`. There is no visual hierarchy -- the cursor position (which changes 60 times/second) has the same weight as the active tool (which changes rarely). The status bar is 26px tall, leaving no breathing room.

### Problem 6: Segmented Controls Are Undersized
**Severity: Medium**

The model-target and view-mode segmented controls use 30px height with 11px font, 10px padding (`Toolbar.module.css` lines 144-171). At the 900px breakpoint, they shrink to 26px/10px/5px. These are primary navigation controls (Floor/Roof/Truss/Sheets and Plan/Front/Rear/Left/Right/Section) but are styled like secondary UI. The active state uses only a white background with a subtle shadow -- insufficient contrast for rapid scanning. The phase view toggle in the sidebar is even smaller at 24px height (`Sidebar.module.css` line 342).

### Problem 7: No Visual Transitions for Panel/Section State Changes
**Severity: Medium**

Sidebar sections toggle between visible/hidden with no animation -- content simply appears/disappears. Panel collapse uses `display: none` (`App.module.css` line 80), causing jarring layout shifts with no transition. The only animation in the sidebar is the chevron rotation at 0.15s (`Sidebar.module.css` line 59). The floor card hover includes `translateY(-1px)` with `--duration-fast` (0.1s), which is functional but not delightful. There are no skeleton/loading states anywhere.

---

## 2. Information Architecture Improvements

### Current User Journey: "Draw a wall on a new floor"
1. Open app (blank canvas, no guidance)
2. Notice "Floors" section in sidebar (if not overlooked)
3. Click "+" to add floor
4. Realize toolbar has a wall tool (13 identical-looking 34x34 icons)
5. Hover each icon to find tooltip "Wall"
6. Click wall icon, draw on canvas
7. No confirmation of success beyond a line appearing

### Improved User Journey: "Draw a wall on a new floor"
1. Open app -- canvas shows centered welcome overlay: "Start with walls. Press W or select the Wall tool."
2. Floor 1 is auto-created and selected (already exists)
3. Wall tool is visually prominent in toolbar -- grouped with structural tools, labeled "Wall (W)"
4. Click wall tool -- status bar transforms to contextual mode: "Click to set wall start point"
5. Draw wall -- toast confirms "Wall created" with undo link
6. Properties panel auto-opens showing wall properties

### Current User Journey: "Switch from Floor to Roof editing"
1. Find the "Floor | Roof | Truss | Sheets" segmented control in the toolbar (small 30px buttons)
2. Click "Roof" -- canvas changes, no transition
3. Sidebar suddenly shows different content (roof-specific sections appear)
4. User is disoriented about what changed

### Improved User Journey: "Switch from Floor to Roof editing"
1. Model-target control is taller (36px) with icons alongside text labels
2. Click "Roof" -- smooth crossfade on canvas (0.2s opacity transition)
3. Sidebar content transitions with staggered fade-in (items appear with 30ms delay each)
4. If no roof exists, canvas shows centered empty state with "Create Roof" CTA button
5. Context header at top of sidebar updates with gentle slide-in

---

## 3. Visual Redesign Direction: Updated Design System Tokens

### New/Modified CSS Custom Properties for `variables.css`

**Colors -- Refined palette with better semantic separation:**

```css
/* Existing to modify */
--color-background: #FAFAF8;            /* keep */
--color-panel-bg: #F5F4F1;              /* slightly warmer, was #F4F3F0 */
--color-panel-bg-alt: #EDECE8;          /* slightly warmer, was #EAEAE7 */
--color-surface-elevated: #FFFFFF;       /* keep */
--color-border: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.07);    /* softer, was 0.08 */
--color-border-subtle: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04); /* softer, was 0.05 */

/* New additions */
--color-surface-glass: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.72);  /* glassmorphism panels */
--color-surface-glass-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
--color-surface-glass-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06), 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);

/* Status semantic colors */
--color-info: #3B82F6;
--color-info-subtle: rgba(59, 130, 246, 0.08);
--color-success: #10B981;
--color-success-subtle: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.08);
--color-warning: #F59E0B;
--color-warning-subtle: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.08);

/* Interaction depth */
--color-hover-overlay: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);    /* subtler hover */
--color-pressed-overlay: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);  /* subtler press */
```

**Spacing -- Add intermediate values:**

```css
--space-3: 3px;    /* new, for tight icon gaps */
--space-6: 6px;    /* new, between --space-xs(4) and --space-sm(8) */
--space-10: 10px;  /* new, between --space-sm(8) and --space-md(12) */
--space-20: 20px;  /* new, between --space-lg(16) and --space-xl(24) */
```

**Shadows -- Add glassmorphism layer:**

```css
--shadow-glass: 0 4px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06), inset 0 0.5px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
--shadow-floating: 0 8px 40px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12), 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
--shadow-toolbar: 0 1px 3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04), 0 4px 12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
```

**Transitions -- Add spring and stagger tokens:**

```css
--ease-out-expo: cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);   /* rename existing --ease-out */
--ease-in-out-soft: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);  /* new, for layout shifts */
--duration-layout: 0.25s;                            /* new, for panel collapses */
--duration-stagger: 30ms;                            /* new, for list item cascade */
```

**Layout -- Slightly wider properties panel:**

```css
--toolbar-height: 52px;      /* reduced from 56px -- tighter, more canvas space */
--sidebar-width: 256px;      /* slightly reduced from 260px, aligns to 8px grid */
--properties-width: 288px;   /* increased from 280px, aligns to 8px grid */
--status-bar-height: 30px;   /* increased from 26px for better readability */
```

---

## 4. Component-Level Upgrades: Top 4 Most Impactful

### Upgrade 1: Toolbar -- Restructure into Two Rows on Narrow Viewports

**File**: `src/ui/Toolbar.module.css`

**Current problem**: Single row, overflow scroll, 30+ items.

**Changes**:

1. Reduce toolbar height from 56px to 52px:
   ```css
   /* line 4 */ height: 52px;  /* was var(--toolbar-height) with 56px */
   ```

2. Increase segmented control height from 30px to 34px, font from 11px to 12px:
   ```css
   .segmentedBtn {
     height: 34px;       /* was 30px */
     padding: 0 12px;    /* was 0 10px */
     font-size: 12px;    /* was 11px */
   }
   ```

3. Active segmented button gets stronger visual signal:
   ```css
   .segmentedBtnActive {
     background: var(--color-surface-elevated);
     color: var(--color-active-glow);
     font-weight: 600;
     box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08), 0 0 0 1px rgba(45, 95, 142, 0.12);
   }
   ```

4. At `@media (max-width: 1100px)`, wrap toolbar into two rows:
   ```css
   @media (max-width: 1100px) {
     .toolbar {
       flex-wrap: wrap;
       height: auto;
       min-height: 52px;
       padding: 4px var(--space-md);
       overflow-x: visible;  /* was auto */
     }
   }
   ```

5. Hide fixture palette labels at 1100px, hide entire fixture group labels at 900px (already partially done, extend it).

6. Add subtle separator gradient between groups instead of hard 1px divider:
   ```css
   .divider {
     width: 1px;
     height: 20px;            /* was 24px */
     background: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, rgba(0,0,0,0.08), transparent);
     margin: 0 var(--space-6);
   }
   ```

**File**: `src/ui/Toolbar.jsx`

No structural JSX changes needed for the CSS-only wrap approach. The existing flex layout with `flex-shrink: 0` on groups will naturally wrap.

### Upgrade 2: Status Bar -- Semantic Segmentation with Visual Hierarchy

**File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.module.css`

**Changes**:

1. Increase status bar height and add visual segmentation:
   ```css
   .statusBar {
     height: 30px;              /* was 26px */
     gap: var(--space-md);      /* was var(--space-xl) -- tighter for segments */
     padding: 0 var(--space-md);
     font-size: 11px;
     background: var(--color-panel-bg);
     border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
   }
   ```

2. Add new CSS classes for status bar segments with different weights:
   ```css
   .statusCoords {
     font-family: var(--font-blueprint);
     color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
     font-size: 10px;
     letter-spacing: 0.03em;
   }

   .statusTool {
     font-family: var(--font-ui);
     font-weight: 600;
     color: var(--color-active-glow);
     font-size: 11px;
     background: var(--color-active-glow-subtle);
     padding: 2px 8px;
     border-radius: 10px;
   }

   .statusContext {
     font-family: var(--font-ui);
     font-weight: 500;
     color: var(--color-text-secondary);
     font-size: 11px;
   }

   .statusBearing {
     font-family: var(--font-blueprint);
     color: var(--color-accent);
     font-weight: 500;
   }
   ```

**File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx` (lines 681-699)

Replace the flat `<span>` list with semantically classed elements:
- Coordinates: use `.statusCoords` (de-emphasized, they change constantly)
- Tool name: use `.statusTool` (pill badge, visually prominent)
- Zoom: use `.statusContext`
- Bearing/selection/phase: use `.statusContext` or `.statusBearing`
- Status message: keep existing `.statusMessage` animation

### Upgrade 3: Sidebar Section Collapse -- Smooth Animated Transitions

**File**: `src/ui/Sidebar.module.css`

**Changes**:

1. Add collapsible content wrapper with CSS-driven height animation:
   ```css
   .sectionContent {
     display: grid;
     grid-template-rows: 1fr;
     transition: grid-template-rows var(--duration-layout) var(--ease-in-out-soft);
   }

   .sectionContentCollapsed {
     grid-template-rows: 0fr;
   }

   .sectionContentInner {
     overflow: hidden;
     min-height: 0;
   }
   ```

   This pattern (grid-template-rows: 1fr to 0fr) animates height from content-size to 0 without needing explicit height values.

2. Add staggered fade-in for section items:
   ```css
   .item {
     animation: fadeInUp 0.15s var(--ease-out) both;
   }
   .item:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0ms; }
   .item:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 30ms; }
   .item:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 60ms; }
   .item:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 90ms; }
   .item:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 120ms; }
   /* ... up to ~10, then cap */
   .item:nth-child(n+10) { animation-delay: 270ms; }
   ```

3. Improve count badge visual presence:
   ```css
   .count {
     font-size: 10px;              /* was 11px */
     padding: 1px 7px;             /* was 0 6px */
     border-radius: 10px;
     line-height: 16px;            /* was 18px */
     font-weight: 700;             /* was 600 */
     letter-spacing: 0.02em;
   }
   ```

**File**: `src/ui/Sidebar.jsx` (lines 52-71, Section component)

Replace `{!collapsed && children}` with the grid-based animation wrapper:
```jsx
<div className={`${styles.sectionContent} ${collapsed ? styles.sectionContentCollapsed : ''}`}>
  <div className={styles.sectionContentInner}>
    {children}
  </div>
</div>
```

This keeps children in DOM always (for animation) but hides them via grid-row collapse.

### Upgrade 4: InputField -- Larger Touch Targets & Better Visual Feedback

**File**: `src/ui/InputField.module.css`

**Changes**:

1. Increase input height from 28px to 32px:
   ```css
   .input {
     height: 32px;           /* was 28px */
     padding: 0 10px;        /* was 0 8px */
     font-size: 13px;        /* was 12px */
     border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
     border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
     background: var(--color-surface-elevated);
     transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s, background 0.15s;
   }
   ```

2. Enhanced focus state with softer glow:
   ```css
   .input:focus {
     border-color: var(--color-active-glow);
     box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(45, 95, 142, 0.10), inset 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03);
     background: #FFFFFF;
   }
   ```

3. Increase suffix visibility:
   ```css
   .suffix {
     font-size: 11px;           /* was 10px */
     color: var(--color-text-secondary);  /* was --color-text-tertiary */
     font-family: var(--font-blueprint);
     font-weight: 500;
   }
   ```

4. Add label alignment improvement:
   ```css
   .label {
     flex: 0 0 84px;           /* was 80px, aligns to 4px grid */
     font-size: 12px;
     font-weight: 500;
     color: var(--color-text-secondary);
     line-height: 32px;        /* match new input height */
   }
   ```

---

## 5. Mobile & Responsive Fixes

### Breakpoint Strategy

| Breakpoint | Target | Current Behavior | Proposed Behavior |
|---|---|---|---|
| <=1200px | Small laptops | 3D preview stacks below canvas | Same + sidebar collapses to icon strip (48px) |
| <=1024px | Tablets landscape | No changes | Sidebar and Properties auto-collapse, toggle with gestures |
| <=900px | Tablets portrait | Toolbar label hiding | Toolbar wraps to 2 rows, status bar hides coordinates |
| <=768px | Large phones | Nothing | Full-screen canvas, bottom sheet for tools, swipe for panels |

### Key CSS Additions

**File**: `src/app/App.module.css`

```css
@media (max-width: 1024px) {
  .layout {
    grid-template-columns: 0px 1fr 0px;
  }
  .sidebar, .properties {
    position: fixed;
    top: var(--toolbar-height);
    bottom: 0;
    z-index: 20;
    width: var(--sidebar-width);
    transform: translateX(-100%);
    transition: transform var(--duration-layout) var(--ease-out-expo);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-floating);
  }
  .sidebar { left: 0; }
  .properties {
    right: 0;
    left: auto;
    width: var(--properties-width);
    transform: translateX(100%);
  }
  .sidebarVisible { transform: translateX(0); }
  .propertiesVisible { transform: translateX(0); }
}
```

**File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx`

Add touch event handlers alongside mouse events. The simplest approach: use pointer events (`onPointerDown/Move/Up`) instead of mouse events. This requires adding `touch-action: none` to the SVG element's CSS and changing the event handler names. The handler logic is identical since pointer events include mouse events.

```css
.svg {
  touch-action: none;  /* add this */
}
```

### Panel Collapse Transitions

Replace `display: none` (`App.module.css` line 80) with transform-based hiding:

```css
.panelHidden {
  width: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  padding: 0;
  border: none;
  transition: width var(--duration-layout) var(--ease-in-out-soft),
              padding var(--duration-layout) var(--ease-in-out-soft);
}
```

This enables smooth slide-in/out instead of jarring pop.

---

## 6. Accessibility & Performance Wins

### Accessibility

1. **Focus management on tool switch**: When user switches tools via keyboard shortcut, move focus to the toolbar button for screen reader announcement. Add `aria-live="polite"` to the status bar.

   **File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.module.css` -- add to `.statusBar`:
   ```css
   /* No CSS change needed, add aria-live="polite" to JSX */
   ```

   **File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx` line 681:
   ```jsx
