# Comprehensive UX Audit & Visual Redesign Plan for Modular Apartment Planner

## 1. UX Audit: 7 Biggest Problems

### Problem 1: Toolbar Density & Horizontal Overflow
**Severity: Critical**

The toolbar packs 30+ interactive elements into a single 56px row: 8 file/clipboard buttons, 4 model-target segments, 6+ view-mode segments, 13 tool buttons, 7 fixture buttons, 6 toggle buttons, plus labels and dividers. The container uses `overflow-x: auto` (`Toolbar.module.css` line 9), meaning on viewports under ~1400px, content clips off-screen with a barely visible 3px scrollbar. Users cannot see all available tools at once, and the scrollbar is so thin (3px, `rgba(0,0,0,0.10)`) it is effectively invisible.

**Evidence**: `Toolbar.module.css` lines 9-20 (overflow + scrollbar), `Toolbar.jsx` lines 204-430 (30+ buttons rendered inline). At the `@media (max-width: 900px)` breakpoint (line 322), labels are hidden and buttons shrink to 30x30, but the row still overflows.

### Problem 2: No Empty States or Onboarding
**Severity: High**

When a new project is created, the canvas shows a blank grid with no guidance. The sidebar sections show "0" count badges but no helpful text. Empty sections in the sidebar render nothing when collapsed or show raw text like "Draw first truss above beams" (`Sidebar.jsx` line 418) without visual affordance (no icon, no illustration, just plain 12px text styled as a clickable `.item`).

The status bar at the bottom is the only contextual guidance, using monospace text at 11px (`SvgCanvas.module.css` lines 23-41) -- easy to miss.

### Problem 3: Touch & Mobile Inoperability
**Severity: High**

The entire interaction model depends on `onMouseDown/Move/Up` events (`SvgCanvas.jsx` lines 151-199). There are no touch event handlers. The toolbar has no hamburger/collapse pattern. Sidebar and Properties panels use `display: none` toggling (`App.module.css` line 80) with no gesture-based reveal. The 260px sidebar + 280px properties panel leave only ~460px for canvas on a 1000px tablet -- and there is no breakpoint that collapses them automatically. The only responsive breakpoints address 3D preview stacking (1200px) and toolbar compaction (1100px, 900px) -- neither collapses the side panels.

### Problem 4: Input Fields Are Too Compact for Precision Work
**Severity: Medium-High**

All form inputs are 28px tall with 12px font (`InputField.module.css` lines 24-36). For a CAD tool where users frequently type precise millimeter values, this is uncomfortably small. The label width is fixed at 80px (`InputField.module.css` line 9), which truncates longer labels. Number inputs use `JetBrains Mono` at 12px -- good choice but too small. The suffix indicator (mm, m) is 10px (`InputField.module.css` line 56) and easy to overlook.

### Problem 5: Status Bar is Information-Dense but Low-Hierarchy
**Severity: Medium**

The status bar (`SvgCanvas.jsx` lines 681-699) dumps 6-10 items in a flat row: coordinates, zoom, view mode, model target, active tool, phase, bearing, selection count. All use the same 11px JetBrains Mono in `--color-text-secondary`. There is no visual hierarchy -- the cursor position (which changes 60 times/second) has the same weight as the active tool (which changes rarely). The status bar is 26px tall, leaving no breathing room.

### Problem 6: Segmented Controls Are Undersized
**Severity: Medium**

The model-target and view-mode segmented controls use 30px height with 11px font, 10px padding (`Toolbar.module.css` lines 144-171). At the 900px breakpoint, they shrink to 26px/10px/5px. These are primary navigation controls (Floor/Roof/Truss/Sheets and Plan/Front/Rear/Left/Right/Section) but are styled like secondary UI. The active state uses only a white background with a subtle shadow -- insufficient contrast for rapid scanning. The phase view toggle in the sidebar is even smaller at 24px height (`Sidebar.module.css` line 342).

### Problem 7: No Visual Transitions for Panel/Section State Changes
**Severity: Medium**

Sidebar sections toggle between visible/hidden with no animation -- content simply appears/disappears. Panel collapse uses `display: none` (`App.module.css` line 80), causing jarring layout shifts with no transition. The only animation in the sidebar is the chevron rotation at 0.15s (`Sidebar.module.css` line 59). The floor card hover includes `translateY(-1px)` with `--duration-fast` (0.1s), which is functional but not delightful. There are no skeleton/loading states anywhere.

