4. **Reduced motion**: Add `prefers-reduced-motion` support:

   **File**: `src/styles/global.css`:
   ```css
   @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
     *, *::before, *::after {
       animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
       transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
     }
   }
   ```

### Performance

1. **CSS `will-change` for animated elements**: Add to elements that animate frequently:

   **File**: `src/ui/Toolbar.module.css`:
   ```css
   .toolbar {
     will-change: auto; /* not needed, remove if present */
   }
   ```

   More importantly, add `contain: content` to sidebar sections and properties panel sections to limit layout recalculation scope:

   ```css
   .section { contain: content; }
   ```

2. **Reduce SVG re-renders**: The `cursorPos` state in `SvgCanvas.jsx` (line 73) triggers a full component re-render on every mouse move. The cursor position is only used in the status bar (lines 682-683). Move cursor display to a separate small component that subscribes to a ref-based value, preventing the entire SVG tree from re-rendering.

3. **Skeleton states for lazy-loaded 3D preview**: The current fallback (`App.module.css` `.previewFallback`, line 63) is a plain text label. Replace with an animated skeleton:

   ```css
   .previewFallback {
     background: var(--color-panel-bg);
     position: relative;
     overflow: hidden;
   }
   .previewFallback::after {
     content: '';
     position: absolute;
     inset: 0;
     background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255,255,255,0.4), transparent);
     animation: shimmer 1.5s infinite;
   }
   @keyframes shimmer {
     0% { transform: translateX(-100%); }
     100% { transform: translateX(100%); }
   }
   ```

---

## 7. Implementation Roadmap: 2-Week Prioritized Plan

### Week 1: Highest Impact, Lowest Risk

**Day 1-2: Design Tokens & Input Fields**
- Update `src/styles/variables.css` with new tokens (colors, spacing, shadows, transitions)
- Update `src/ui/InputField.module.css` (height 28->32, font 12->13, suffix 10->11)
- Update `src/ui/PropertiesPanel.module.css` (segment controls 24->28 height, delete/action buttons 30->34)
- Estimated files: 3 | Risk: Very low (CSS-only, no logic changes)

**Day 2-3: Toolbar Segmented Controls & Dividers**
- Update `src/ui/Toolbar.module.css` segmented buttons (height 30->34, font 11->12, active state glow)
- Replace divider styling with gradient approach
- Add `flex-wrap: wrap` at 1100px breakpoint
- Estimated files: 1 | Risk: Low (CSS-only, test layout at breakpoints)

**Day 3-4: Status Bar Redesign**
- Add new CSS classes in `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.module.css` (statusCoords, statusTool, statusContext)
- Update JSX in `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx` lines 681-699 to use semantic classes
- Increase height to 30px, add `aria-live="polite"`
- Estimated files: 2 | Risk: Low

**Day 4-5: Sidebar Animated Collapse**
- Add grid-based collapse CSS to `src/ui/Sidebar.module.css`
- Update `Section` component in `src/ui/Sidebar.jsx` to use wrapper pattern
- Add staggered fade-in for items
- Test with all section types (floors, walls, phases, roof sub-sections)
- Estimated files: 2 | Risk: Medium (animation timing, ensure scroll behavior)

### Week 2: Medium Impact, Higher Complexity

**Day 6-7: Panel Collapse Transitions**
- Replace `display: none` in `src/app/App.module.css` with width-based collapse
- Add transition timing to sidebar and properties panel show/hide
- Test grid layout recalculation during transition
- Estimated files: 1-2 | Risk: Medium (grid layout interaction during animation)

**Day 7-8: Responsive Breakpoints**
- Add 1024px breakpoint to `src/app/App.module.css` (fixed position panels with transforms)
- Add slide-in panel visibility classes
- Update `src/app/App.jsx` to pass `sidebarVisible`/`propertiesVisible` class when toggled at narrow widths
- Estimated files: 2-3 | Risk: Medium

**Day 8-9: Accessibility Pass**
- Update `--color-text-tertiary` contrast in `src/styles/variables.css`
- Add `prefers-reduced-motion` media query in `src/styles/global.css`
- Convert sidebar `.item` divs to buttons in `src/ui/Sidebar.jsx`
- Add `aria-live` to status bar in `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx`
- Estimated files: 4 | Risk: Low

**Day 9-10: Performance & Polish**
- Extract cursor position display to a separate component (avoid re-rendering SVG tree)
- Add skeleton shimmer to 3D preview fallback in `src/app/App.module.css`
- Add `contain: content` to sidebar sections
- Add pointer events to SVG for basic touch support in `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx` and `SvgCanvas.module.css`
- Final visual QA across breakpoints
- Estimated files: 3-4 | Risk: Medium (cursor extraction is a refactor)

### Total Estimated Scope
- **Files modified**: ~12 unique files
- **New files**: 0 (all changes within existing CSS Modules and JSX)
- **Breaking changes**: 0 (all changes are additive or CSS-level)
- **Highest-impact single change**: Toolbar segmented control sizing + wrapping (Day 2-3)
- **Most delightful change**: Sidebar section collapse animation (Day 4-5)

---

### Critical Files for Implementation
- `C:\Users\johnm\modular apartment planner\src\styles\variables.css` - Foundation: all design token changes (colors, spacing, transitions, layout) propagate to every component via CSS custom properties
- `C:\Users\johnm\modular apartment planner\src\ui\Toolbar.module.css` - Highest-visibility component: segmented control sizing, toolbar wrapping, divider styling, responsive breakpoints
- `C:\Users\johnm\modular apartment planner\src\ui\Sidebar.module.css` - Most impactful animation work: section collapse transitions, item stagger, count badge, section header refinements
- `C:\Users\johnm\modular apartment planner\src\renderers\SvgCanvas.module.css` - Status bar redesign with semantic hierarchy, toast refinements, canvas overlay controls
- `C:\Users\johnm\modular apartment planner\src\app\App.module.css` - Layout grid: panel collapse transitions, responsive breakpoints for side panels, 3D preview skeleton

